To evaluate the final model for an individual, we dichotomized the score into ‘test positive’ versus ‘test negative’ using alternative thresholds of 5; 10; 20; 30; 40; 50 and 60% for a positive test result. For positive test cases, we calculated false positive rate (the proportion of test positive cases who did not experience work disability), detection rate (the proportion of work disability cases who were test positive) and the ratio of true to false positives. The formulas were as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
